last_episode_to_air.name: Destroying Miami
last_episode_to_air.overview: Kenan, Gary, Mika, Tami and Phil head to Miami for some fun, but with love in the air, they find trouble. Things don't go smoothly for Rick and Loretta, who stay home to take care of the girls.

name: Kenan
overview: The recently widowed host of Atlanta's No. 2 morning show struggles to balance his job and his young daughters despite all the “help” he gets from his grifter father-in-law and his brother/assistant/manager/house guest.
tagline: Raising two kids is a three-man job.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: A recently-widowed dad tries to raise his kids with his persistent father-in-law.

episodes.name: Hard News
episodes.overview: Kenan, Rick and Gary go to great lengths to uncover what they think is a deep, dark secret Cori was hiding. Mika believes the morning show should cover more hard news stories.

episodes.name: The Fourth Hour
episodes.overview: Kenan struggles with his increased work schedule when "Wake Up With Kenan!" adds a fourth hour. Rick encourages Kenan to get tough and say "no" more often. Gary suspects that Tami has her eye on Kenan's job and takes matters into his own hands.

episodes.name: Flirting
episodes.overview: With Gary's encouragement, Kenan agrees to get back into the dating world slowly through flirting. Rick takes Aubrey and Birdie for a spa day and can't help but join in.

episodes.name: Flipp'd
episodes.overview: When Kenan's former boy bandmate-turned-huge popstar comes to town, Kenan finds himself doubting Gary's effectiveness as a manager and contemplates a change. Mika gives Aubrey and Birdie a lesson in feminism and the art of persuasion.

episodes.name: You Go, Squirrel!
episodes.overview: Kenan has some odd encounters with a squirrel that he believes might be Cori's spirit. Rick and Gary think they've missed Kenan's birthday and try to organize an impromptu surprise party.

episodes.name: Kenan's Mom
episodes.overview: When Kenan's mom, Bobbi, comes for a visit, it's apparent she's developed a new sense of independence and Kenan finds himself competing for her attention.

episodes.name: Wednesday's Gal
episodes.overview: Mika is determined to use the show's annual "Wednesday's Gal" wedding segment to generate desperately needed advertising revenue for the station. With love in the air, Kenan contemplates his romantic future.

episodes.name: Teachers' Strike
episodes.overview: When the teachers go on strike, everyone has to pitch in to keep the kids occupied. Rick sets up a unique schoolroom in the morning show conference room.

episodes.name: Hair Show
episodes.overview: Kenan, Rick, Gary and Mika prepare the girls for the annual Atlanta Hair Show but Kenan is feeling the pressure because it was one of Cori's favorite events. Gary secures an offer for a sitcom, but Kenan must contemplate a move to Los Angeles. Cori's mother, Tasha, pays a visit.

episodes.name: Dating App
episodes.overview: With Gary’s help, Kenan signs up for a dating app that he might not be ready for while Rick has an interesting date of his own. Mika and Pam strategize to help Tami when she is caught in an unflattering situation by a tabloid photographer.

episodes.name: Work Friends
episodes.overview: Kenan offends Tami when he reveals that he only sees her as a colleague and not as a friend. Gary and Rick encourage Birdie to use TikTok before she’s ready, which lands her in real trouble at school.

episodes.name: Those Chops Pop
episodes.overview: Kenan struggles to define his personal and professional relationship with Mika. Rick searches for his passion and makes an unexpected enemy.

episodes.name: Ghosts of Boyfriends Past
episodes.overview: Kenan believes he should help Mika with her boyfriend troubles, whether she needs it or not. Pam and Gary have a crush on the same woman and risk their friendship to be with her.

episodes.name: Hustle And Flow
episodes.overview: Kenan and Aubrey clash when he refuses to see that she's growing up. While Gary pursues a controversial revenue stream on social media, Mika, Tami and Pam are inspired to show him the downside.

episodes.name: Workaholic
episodes.overview: Mika finds herself at odds with Kenan, Pam and Tami when they accuse her of being a workaholic. Gary unintentionally meets a woman that he really likes and struggles with how to tell her.

episodes.name: The Whole Enchilada
episodes.overview: Kenan has doubts about introducing his secret girlfriend, Janay, to his family. Pam pursues a new business opportunity with Gary, but her competitive nature gets in the way of her own success.

episodes.name: Moving Violation
episodes.overview: When their mom, Bobbi, decides to sell the family home, Kenan and Gary must clear the basement of their childhood memorabilia, leading Gary to evaluate his goals in life.

episodes.name: Destroying Miami
episodes.overview: Kenan, Gary, Mika, Tami and Phil head to Miami for some fun, but with love in the air, they find trouble. Things don't go smoothly for Rick and Loretta, who stay home to take care of the girls.
